      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The worst-case scenario for dropping your warfarin without supervision is a life-threatening blood clot, which is exactly what the medication is there to prevent. Feeling \"100%\" is not a substitute for laboratory confirmation of your clotting factors. You should absolutely try to get a quick check-in with your doctor, but in the meantime, stick strictly to the prescribed 5mg dose.",
      "source": "target",
